To simplify \(\frac{\tfrac{4}{5}}{\tfrac{8}{15}}\), multiply by the reciprocal of the denominator:

\[
\frac{\tfrac{4}{5}}{\tfrac{8}{15}}
= \frac{4}{5}\times\frac{15}{8}
= \frac{4\cdot15}{5\cdot8}
= \frac{60}{40}
= \frac{3}{2}.
\]

To simplify \(\frac{-\tfrac{9}{10}}{3}\), rewrite the division as multiplication by the reciprocal of 3:

\[
\frac{-\tfrac{9}{10}}{3}
= -\frac{9}{10}\times\frac{1}{3}
= -\frac{9}{30}
= -\frac{3}{10}.
\]
